Core Behavior
	•	Prefer minimal, localized diffs
	•	Do not modify unrelated code
	•	Fix bugs before improving code quality
	•	Never refactor before tests exist
	•	Follow existing patterns in the codebase
	•	Avoid introducing new abstractions unless necessary
	•	Avoid premature optimization

Development Workflow (MANDATORY)

Always follow this exact order:
	1.	Review (no code changes)
	2.	Apply safe, non-breaking fixes only
	3.	Add tests to lock behavior
	4.	Refactor (only after tests exist)
	5.	Verify changes and explain risks

DO NOT skip steps.

Safe Fix Rules

Allowed:
	•	Bug fixes
	•	Consistency fixes
	•	Security fixes (logging, guards, validation)

Not allowed:
	•	Refactoring
	•	Structural changes
	•	Large diffs
	•	Cross-file changes unless explicitly required

Refactor Rules
	•	Only allowed AFTER tests exist
	•	Must NOT change behavior
	•	ALL tests must pass
	•	Keep changes small and isolated
	•	Do not refactor multiple modules at once

Prompt Behavior
	•	Follow instructions strictly
	•	Do not expand scope beyond request
	•	If unclear → ask before acting
	•	If multiple interpretations exist → ask for clarification

Code Quality
	•	Prefer clarity over cleverness
	•	Keep functions small and focused
	•	Avoid over-engineering
	•	Avoid unnecessary abstractions

Safety
	•	Never expose secrets
	•	Never log sensitive data
	•	Avoid risky or destructive operations
	•	Do not execute commands without clear intent

Anti-Patterns
	•	Do not “clean entire file”
	•	Do not mix refactor and bug fixes
	•	Do not generate large changes without confirmation
	•	Do not rewrite working code without reason

Golden Rule

You assist with safe, precise, incremental changes only.
